<h1>CLI reference</h1>

<p>
    Once <code>nxt</code> is on PATH (installed via the platform script), every command
    accepts <code>--help</code>.
</p>

<h2><code>nxt new &lt;name&gt;</code></h2>
<p>Scaffolds a new app from the <code>Nxt.Templates</code> template package.</p>
<pre><code>nxt new my-app
cd my-app
nxt dev</code></pre>

<h2><code>nxt dev</code></h2>
<p>Runs the app with hot reload (wraps <code>dotnet watch</code>).</p>
<table>
    <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>What</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>--project &lt;path&gt;</code></td><td>Run a specific .csproj instead of the current directory's.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--port &lt;n&gt;</code> / <code>-p</code></td><td>Bind on <code>http://localhost:&lt;n&gt;</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--urls &lt;urls&gt;</code></td><td>Full URL(s) to bind, e.g. <code>http://0.0.0.0:5099;https://0.0.0.0:7099</code>.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h2><code>nxt build</code></h2>
<p>Publishes the app for production AND prerenders every static page to disk.</p>
<table>
    <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>What</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>--configuration &lt;name&gt;</code></td><td>Build configuration. Default <code>Release</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--output &lt;dir&gt;</code></td><td>Publish destination. Default <code>./publish</code>.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
<p>
    The SSG pass works by setting <code>NXT_PRERENDER=1</code> and launching the published
    DLL — the runtime detects the flag, renders every static-marked route into the cache (and
    to disk if <code>StaticOutputDirectory</code> is set), then exits without binding a port.
</p>

<h2><code>nxt start</code></h2>
<p>Runs the published build in production mode. <code>--port</code> / <code>--urls</code> as above.</p>

<h2><code>nxt publish</code></h2>
<p>
    Three publish modes selected by flag — combine them in one invocation if you like.
    Every mode runs <code>dotnet publish</code> first so the output is fresh.
</p>
<table>
    <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>What</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>--static &lt;dir&gt;</code> / <code>-s</code></td>
            <td>Boots the published app on a random local port, crawls every page reachable
            from <code>/</code> via internal <code>&lt;a href&gt;</code> links, and saves
            each response as <code>&lt;dir&gt;/&lt;path&gt;/index.html</code>. Also copies
            <code>wwwroot/</code>. Drop the result on any static host.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--image &lt;tag&gt;</code> / <code>-i</code></td>
            <td>Generates a <code>Dockerfile</code> (only if missing) and runs
            <code>docker build -t &lt;tag&gt;</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--push &lt;registry/tag&gt;</code></td>
            <td>After <code>--image</code>, also tag (if different) and
            <code>docker push</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--docker-context &lt;path&gt;</code></td>
            <td>Override the docker build context (default: project dir). Use the repo root
            if your csproj has <code>ProjectReference</code>s outside the project dir.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--bundle &lt;path&gt;</code> / <code>-b</code></td>
            <td>Tars the <code>publish/</code> folder. Compression chosen by extension —
            <code>.tar.gz</code>, <code>.tar.bz2</code>, <code>.tar.xz</code>.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<pre><code># Export the docs as static HTML for Cloudflare Pages
nxt publish --static ./out

# Build &amp; push a Docker image
nxt publish --image myapp:v1 --push registry.fly.io/myapp:v1

# Tarball for scp
nxt publish --bundle ./dist/myapp.tar.gz</code></pre>

<h2><code>nxt skill</code></h2>
<p>
    Installs a Claude skill — a markdown file with YAML frontmatter that teaches an
    AI assistant how to use Nxt — into your project's
    <code>.claude/skills/</code> folder (or globally to
    <code>~/.claude/skills/</code>). The bundled skills live in
    <code>/Ai/skills/</code> in this repo.
</p>
<pre><code># list what's available
nxt skill list

# install the "nxt" skill into the current project
nxt skill add nxt

# install globally so it's available to every project on this machine
nxt skill add nxt --global</code></pre>
<table>
    <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>What</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>--global</code> / <code>-g</code></td><td>Install to <code>~/.claude/skills/</code> instead of <code>./.claude/skills/</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--force</code> / <code>-f</code></td><td>Overwrite the destination if it already exists.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--output &lt;path&gt;</code></td><td>Custom destination directory.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h2><code>nxt update</code></h2>
<p>
    Downloads the latest source from GitHub, re-packs Runtime/CLI/Templates, clears NuGet
    caches, and reinstalls the CLI + template in one step.
</p>
<table>
    <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>What</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>--repo &lt;url&gt;</code></td><td>GitHub repo URL. Default <code>https://github.com/Tyler-Harker/Nxt</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--branch &lt;name&gt;</code></td><td>Branch or tag. Default <code>master</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--keep-source</code></td><td>Don't delete the downloaded source after install.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
